pl.myrecipebasket.model

Class Recipe

  • java.lang.Object
    • pl.myrecipebasket.model.Recipe
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Recipe
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Object Recipe represents a recipe placed on an external web site that User finds worth storing for later use.

    A Recipe has:
    • rName - recipe name (e.g. "Recipe for homemade pancakes")
    • rDescription - recipe description (e.g. "This is my favorite recipe for homemade pancakes. Perfect taste and healthy ingredients")
    • rUrl - url address of web site where recipe is originally stored
    • rDate - time stamp when Recipe has been added to MyRecipeBasket database
    • UpVote & DownVote - information about number of supporting and opposing Votes left by MyRecipeBasket community
    • isShared - a flag which changes its value if User who added Recipe wants it to be shared with other MyRecipeBasket Users
    • rCategories - a list of Categories that are assigned to Recipe
    • usrWhoAddedRecipe - a reference to User who created Recipe
    • votes - a list of Votes left by MyRecipeBasket community
    • comments - a list of Comments left by MyRecipeBasket community
    • usrWhoAddedRecipeToFavourites - a list of Users who added this recipe to their favorite section
    See Also:
    User, Vote, Comment, Serialized Form
